#.  Overview
#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:335
msgid "Speech and Braille are available at the beginning of installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:337
#, no-wrap
msgid "Overview of the installation process"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:342
msgid "The installer first probes the existing drives and partitions to assess the possibilities and options of installation and let you choose between an automatic or manual preparation of the partitions used by Slint."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:347
msgid "If you choose 'manual' you are presented the Linux partitions where Slint could be installed (size at least 50G), select one of them and choose the type of the file system that the installer will create in it: btrfs, ext4 or xfs as mentioned in <<prepare_partitions_for_Slint,Optionally prepare partitions for Slint>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:350
msgid "If you choose 'auto' you are presented the drives where Slint could be installed (size at least 50G), and the file system will be of type btrfs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:354
msgid "In case of btrfs sub-volumes will created for \"/\" and \"/home\" with files compressed, and /swap to host a swap file. 'Copy on write' will ease making snapshots and possibly revert a faulty system update. Tools to manage the snapshots are included in Slint."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:358
msgid "In both modes the user chooses which existing Linux and Windows partitions will be automatically mounted after booting Slint, and their mount points names, easing access to exiting systems and data from Slint."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:364
msgid "Then the user is proposed to encrypt the root system partition, to prevent data steal in case of loss or theft of the machine or the drive where Slint is installed. If accepted the installer records the passphrase allowing to unlock this partition. The user will when typing it at boot time when requested by GRUB to display the boot menu."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:369
msgid "After all that the installer summarizes your choices and let you confirm them or not. Up to this point no modification will have been done to the installed systems and data so you can safely deny, then type start again or just reboot without any harm."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:373
msgid "Then auto partitioning is done case occurring, the Slint root partition is encrypted if requested, the root partition is formatted and the first software packages are installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:376
msgid "If you opted for an encrypted disk you type the passphrase that will be used to unlock the drive at each boot up."
msgstr "Se você optou por um disco criptografado você digita a senha que será usada para desbloquear a unidade em cada inicialização."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:379
msgid "You choose a password for the user \"root.\" This is the system administrator, who has all privileges."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:381
msgid "You also set the login name and password of a regular user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:386
msgid "You indicate if you will need accessible Braille output, and whether you want to log in text or graphical mode. If you used the language English (USA) during installation you choose the language to use in the installed system, else the installer sets the same as during installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:390
msgid "The installer attempts to establish an Internet connection, and if successful proposes a time zone corresponding to your geographical location that you confirm, else select one in a list."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:394
msgid "You are asked if you will need Braille, then if you prefer to start in a console or in a graphical unless you used speech during installation or need Braille: then you will land in a console after reboot, for safety."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:396
msgid "The installer then creates a swap file. This can take a long time, please be patient."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:400
msgid "The packages are installed on the drive. If an Internet connection has been established it downloads and install the most recent version of each package, including those provided since the release of the ISO image."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:403
msgid "Installation of all packages takes about 10 to 40 minutes depending on the hardware."
msgstr "A instalação de todos os pacotes leva cerca de 10 a 40 minutos, dependendo do hardware."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:407
msgid "You will be asked to select a desktop (even if you start in a console at first) among fvm, lxqt, mate and wmaker. Other choices will be available after installation typing 'xwmconfig' if you start in a console"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:411
msgid "Then, the system is configured and the GRUB boot manager installed. Slint can boot in both Legacy and EFI modes. The boot menu will include a \"rescue\" boot entry to detect and allow any installed OS to be booted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:413
msgid "You can display a preview of the boot menu before rebooting."
msgstr ""

